com.ibm.team.repository.client.util
Interface IPropertyChangeEvent

All Superinterfaces:
IEvent
All Known Implementing Classes:
PropertyChangeEvent
public interface IPropertyChangeEvent
extends IEvent

A description of a property change that has occurred for some object and originated from some event source.

Typically an event source that fires property change events, will declare property constants in its interface and provide documentation of which API calls will cause those properties to change. Listeners for property change events will be registered by passing the property constant as a category argument when calling IEventSource#addGenericListener.

Since:
0.5

getOldValue

java.lang.Object getOldValue()
Returns the value of the object's property before the change occurred. For a list-based property, this represents a value, or a list of values, removed from the list. For a move, this represents the old position of the moved value.

Returns:
the old value of the object's property, which may be null

getNewValue

java.lang.Object getNewValue()
Returns the value of the object's property after the change occurred. For a list-based property, this represents a value, or a list of values, added to the list.

Returns:
the new value of the object's property, which may be null

getPosition

int getPosition()
Returns the position within a list-based property at which the change occurred. It returns IPropertyChangeEvent.NO_INDEX when not applicable.

Returns:
the position at which the change occurred.

getData

java.lang.Object getData()
Returns extra data that was attached to the event. Particular event sources that fire property change events should document what the extra data is.

Returns:
the extra data that was attached to the event.
